{{Infobox person | name = Ashley Gable | image = | caption = | birth_date = | birth_name = | birth_place = United States | occupation = {{Flat list| * Screenwriter * producer}} | years_active = 1996–present }} '''Ashley Gable''' is an American [[screenwriter]] and producer who has worked on a variety of well-known television series including ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]'' and ''[[Person of Interest (TV series)|Person of Interest]]''. She was an executive producer on the [[CBS]] crime drama ''[[The Mentalist]]'' for its first four seasons.
==Career== Gable's television career began in 1996 when she was recruited onto the writing staff of the [[Buffy the Vampire Slayer (season 1)|first season]] of [[Joss Whedon|Joss Whedon's]] ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]''. She (and her then-writing partner Thomas A. Swyden) wrote two of the twelve episodes for the season.
Gable has worked on a number of other shows as a writer and producer, including ''[[The Invisible Man (2000 TV series)|The Invisible Man]]'', ''[[Family Law (TV series)|Family Law]]'', ''[[The Division]]'', ''[[Strong Medicine]]'', ''[[Crossing Jordan]]'', ''[[New Amsterdam (2008 TV series)|New Amsterdam]]'' and ''[[Vegas (2012 TV series)|Vegas]]''. In 2008 she was hired to work on ''[[The Mentalist]]'' as a co-executive producer under creator [[Bruno Heller]] and became an executive producer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/ashley-gable/221601|title=Ashley Gable: Biography, Latest News & Videos|work=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=April 2, 2011}}</ref> She left that show after four seasons and subsequently served as co-executive producer on the CBS drama series ''[[Person of Interest (TV series)|Person of Interest]]''.
